Makes about 24Ingredients:270g (2 cups) cake flour10ml (2 tsp) baking powderPinch of sugar5ml (1 tsp) bicarbonate of sodaPinch of salt100g butter, chilled and cubed300ml buttermilk125ml ( cup) Nutella Just desserts: Caramel hot cross Chelsea bunsMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C and line a baking tray with baking paper.2) Sift the flour, baking powder, sugar, bicarbonate of soda and salt into a large mixing bowl and mix in the butter using your fingertips until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.3) Mix in the buttermilk and stir until just combined - don't overmix. Using a knife, swirl the Nutella into the dough.4) Drop a large spoonful of dough onto the baking tray and bake until the tops are slightly golden, about 12 - 15 minutes. Remove and allow to cool. Best eaten warm with extra blob of Nutella on the side.